    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine 60ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[90ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]<strong> </span>milk</strong> with your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and 2 tbsp [<span class=\"text-purple\">3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> in a measuring jug, then whisk until you get a smooth batter – this is your <strong>spiced batter</strong></p><p>Pour the<strong> spiced batter</strong> over the floured onions and give everything a mix so they are nicely coated – these are your<strong> battered onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
